<!--
VOICING PLAN (4106 — Christ The Lord Is Risen Today, F major):
- All B notes use accid.ges="f" (key sig Bb). Natural B in bar 11 uses accid="n".
- Phrase 1 (1-4): Lighter — quartal opening (F4-Bb4), 2-3 note RH, 3-note LH.
- Phrase 2 (5-8): Fuller — 7th chord additions (FΔ7, Dm7, Gm7), 3-note RH/LH.
- Phrase 3 (9-12): Development — chromatic color (Bdim passing, Am substitution for Cm/A°),
  climax in bar 12 with C major spread across both staves high register.
- Phrase 4 (13-16): Recapitulation + Final IV→V→I cadence Gm7→F.
- Bar 11: =B (Bnatural in key of F) explicitly spelled out with accid="n".

VOICE LEADING HIGHLIGHTS:
- Bar 2→3: RH C5-F5 → Bb4-D5 half-step approach to F/Am (smooth chromatic motion).
- Bar 7: RH active eighth-note motion in Am/Bb passage mirrors bar 3 but richer.
- Bar 10: RH descent D5→C5→Bb4→D5→G4 tracks the melody's stepwise drop.
- Bar 12: Full C major spread reaching G5 — textural peak of the arrangement.
- Bar 15: Rapid Gm↔F↔Am oscillation in last phrase reflects the cadential approach.
- Contrary motion throughout: LH anchors while RH reaches upward at climaxes.

TEXTURE ARC:
- Bars 1-4: Light opening — quartal RH, 3-note LH, establishing F major brightness.
- Bars 5-8: Growing — 7th chords, richer RH, ascending LH.
- Bars 9-12: Climax — bar 12 peaks with G5 in RH, full 4-note LH. Broadest range.
- Bars 13-16: Convergent close — sus4 color, then direct I resolution. F3-F5 final spread.
-->
